- AngularJS Supports Two Types Of Storages.

1.localStorage
2. sessionStorage

localStorage.
    localStorages we must delete explicitely.

sessionStorage.
    when we close the "browser / session" automatically session will be expaired (data will be lost).


- we can work withe storages by using "ngstorage" module.

- ngstorage module contains two predefined objects.

    1.$localStorage

    2.$sessionStorage


- $localStorage used to work with the localStorage.

- $sessionStorage used to work with the sessionStorage.
